"ngram\": \"his hotel room\", \"from\": 8850, \"to\": 8864}, {\"ngram\": \"Dubai\", \"from\": 8868, \"to\": 8873}, {\"ngram\": \"more than two dozen operatives\", \"from\": 8920, \"to\": 8950}, {\"ngram\": \"security cameras\", \"from\": 8971, \"to\": 8987}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel\", \"from\": 8991, \"to\": 9000}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their fake identities were exposed and their pictures were published and broadcast globally.\", \"from\": 9002, \"to\": 9094, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their fake identities\", \"from\": 9002, \"to\": 9023}, {\"ngram\": \"their pictures\", \"from\": 9041, \"to\": 9055}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite mishaps and setbacks, there is still widespread support in Israel for the tactic.\", \"from\": 9096, \"to\": 9185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9163, \"end\": 9169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.636532831398473e-55, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mishaps\", \"from\": 9104, \"to\": 9111}, {\"ngram\": \"setbacks\", \"from\": 9116, \"to\": 9124}, {\"ngram\": \"widespread support\", \"from\": 9141, \"to\": 9159}, {\"ngram\": \"the tactic\", \"from\": 9174, \"to\": 9184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In internal government debates, Mossad has at times argued that killing militant leaders saves lives by avoiding an all-out war with far more casualties, according to \\\"Rise and Kill First\\\" by Ronen Bergman, a detailed history of Israel's assassination operations.\", \"from\": 9186, \"to\": 9449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9218, \"end\": 9224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6090035023443812e-124, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}, {\"begin\": 9384, \"end\": 9391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_Bergman\", \"score\": 0.9999350143778352, \"rank\": 6.498984516489342e-05, \"text\": \"Bergman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_Bergman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ingmar_Bergman\"}, {\"begin\": 9415, \"end\": 9421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.636532831398473e-55, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"internal government debates\", \"from\": 9189, \"to\": 9216}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 9232, \"to\": 9237}, {\"ngram\": \"militant leaders\", \"from\": 9258, \"to\": 9274}, {\"ngram\": \"lives\", \"from\": 9281, \"to\": 9286}, {\"ngram\": \"an all-out war\", \"from\": 9299, \"to\": 9313}, {\"ngram\": \"far more casualties\", \"from\": 9319, \"to\": 9338}, {\"ngram\": \"First\", \"from\": 9368, \"to\": 9373}, {\"ngram\": \"a detailed history\", \"from\": 9393, \"to\": 9411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But former senior intelligence and military officers also have said that only difficult political compromises with Palestinian adversaries - not covert operations - ultimately will ensure Israel's security.\", \"from\": 9450, \"to\": 9656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9565, \"end\": 9576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999993883368058, \"rank\": 6.116636185666712e-07, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 9638, \"end\": 9644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.636532831398473e-55, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}], \"noun_phrases